echo "performance" | sudo tee /sys/devices/system/cpu/cpu*/cpufreq/scaling_governor
nohup bash ./../run_wwb_grid.sh --long-prompt > run_wwb_grid.long_prompt.out 2>&1 && bash ./../run.benchmark.sh > run.benchmark.out 2>&1


# 1. Change layout of kvcache block zp+scale, make them contiguous for better memory access pattern.
# This improves 0.11 density performance by ~6%. from baseline:
# [total]: PA_causal seq_len=32768 , trunks=1, density 0.11, compressKVCache True, MFU 14,246 GFLOPS, latency: 70.674 ms, meet: 0.47
# to:
# [total]: PA_causal seq_len=32768 , trunks=1, density 0.11, compressKVCache True, MFU 17,263 GFLOPS, latency: 58.322 ms, meet: 0.58
# [total]: PA_causal seq_len=32768 , trunks=1, density 0.11, compressKVCache True, MFU 15,340 GFLOPS, latency: 65.633 ms, meet: 0.51
# [total]: PA_causal seq_len=32768 , trunks=1, density 0.11, compressKVCache True, MFU 14,890 GFLOPS, latency: 67.617 ms, meet: 0.50


# packed bitmask for sparsity, - tried, no significant perf gain.
# [total]: PA_causal seq_len=32768 , trunks=1, density 0.11, compressKVCache True, MFU 14,154 GFLOPS, latency: 71.135 ms, meet: 0.47

# prefetch gating by block mask, - tried, no significant perf gain in case of 32k prompt with 0.11 density becasue there is no tailing.

# removing tail masking for full blocks only. - Already did for int8 path. Can apply to fp16 path as well.


Other options may consider:
1. Load sparse_mask_base into registers or SLM, and them use the cache in skip_load.
2. Increase kv_step from 16 to like 32 or 64, to reduce synchronizing overhead. This may involve load the macro step of K/Vs into SLM.
3. packed bitmask for sparsity,

